ALGORITHM: 
Step 1: Start the Apache Tomcat Server or any compatible JSP container. 
Step 2: Create a JSP file (welcome.jsp) using a text editor or IDE (like Eclipse/NetBeans). 
Step 3: Write the HTML structure along with JSP scriptlets to process user input. 
Step 4: Create a form page (index.html or form.jsp) that collects input (e.g., name and email). 
Step 5: Use JSP to retrieve the request parameters and display them dynamically. 
Step 6: Deploy the files inside the webapps folder of Tomcat (e.g., /webapps/JSPDemo/). 
Step 7: Start Tomcat and open the form page in a browser. 
Step 8: Submit the form and observe the dynamic output from the JSP script. 
Step 9: Stop the server after testing.


form.jsp (Input Page)
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Simple JSP Form</title>
    <style>
        body {
            background-color: #f0f8ff;
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
        }
        .form-container {
            width: 300px;
            margin: 80px auto;
            padding: 20px;
            background-color: #fff;
            border: 2px solid #ddd;
            border-radius: 10px;
        }
        input[type="text"], input[type="submit"] {
            width: 90%;
            padding: 10px;
            margin: 8px 0;
        }
        input[type="submit"] {
            background-color: #4CAF50;
            color: white;
            border: none;
            cursor: pointer;
        }
        input[type="submit"]:hover {
            background-color: #45a049;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
<div class="form-container">
    <form action="welcome.jsp" method="post">
        <label for="username">Enter Your Name:</label><br>
        <input type="text" name="username" id="username" required><br>
        <input type="submit" value="Submit">
    </form>
</div>
</body>
</html>


welcome.jsp (Output Page)
<%@ page language="java" contentType="text/html; charset=UTF-8" %>
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Welcome</title>
    <style>
        body {
            background-color: #e0ffff;
            text-align: center;
            font-family: 'Segoe UI', sans-serif;
            color: #333;
        }
        .message {
            margin-top: 100px;
            font-size: 24px;
            color: #006400;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="message">
        <%
            String username = request.getParameter("username");

            if(username != null && !username.trim().equals("")) {
        %>
                Welcome, <%= username %>! Thanks for using JSP.
        <%
            } else {
        %>
                No name entered. Please go back and try again.
        <%
            }
        %>
    </div>
</body>
</html>

